I also tried iterating the classLoader->classSegments to look for the J9Class* for the romClass we have in hand via:
                                        J9MemorySegment *segment = classLoader->classSegments;
                                        while (NULL != segment) {
                                                if (MEMORY_TYPE_RAM_CLASS == (segment->type & MEMORY_TYPE_RAM_CLASS)) {
                                                        J9Class* segClass = *((J9Class**)segment->heapBase);
                                                        while (NULL != segClass) {
                                                                if (segClass->romClass == romClass) {
                                                                        fprintf(stderr, "Filip: Found RAMClass = %p\n", segClass);
                                                                }
                                                                segClass = segClass->nextClassInSegment;
                                                        }
                                                }
                                                segment = segment->nextSegmentInClassLoader;
                                        }

And it was not printing anything. I assume there has to be a J9Class* for every J9ROMClass* we have in hand, right? Not sure if the above algorithm covers all cases.

